name: The Knowledge House Fellowship, Inc.
content: We are excited to announce that The Knowledge House has been selected as a 2023 Tech Equity Collective Impact Fund Recipient! Tech Equity Collective, an initiative started by Google, accelerates Black innovation and representation in tech by bringing together community and industry partners to create programs and experiences that lead to tangible progress of Black tech innovators.The TEC Impact Fund, with the support of Goodie Nation, provides financial funding to US Black-in-Tech organizations equipping aspiring Black professionals, focused on core engineering and technical roles, with the skills and tools to thrive in tech. We are proud Tech Equity Collective Advocates! Learn more → https://techequitycollective.com#Google #BlackInTech #TECImpactFund #ImpactFund #WCW #WomenCrushWednesday #POC

content: “We are in the middle of a dramatic and broad technological and economic shift in which software companies are poised to take over large swathes of the economy. name: The Knowledge House Fellowship, Inc.
content: Thank you all for attending our 2022 Corporate Partners Reception presented by Accenture! The whole experience was an example of how corporations can work with TKH to support Black and Brown aspiring #technologists into careers and help them stay in jobs with opportunities for #advancement.We’re so grateful to Rah Thomas, Selena Hill, Abby Jo Sigal, Marcus Felder and Neela Pal for inspiring conversations regarding the #TechIndustry and its future.Become a part of our #TKHFamily by joining our #Giving Clubs today! Link in bio.#ExpandOpportuntiy #techcareers #techevent #techinnovation

name: The Knowledge House Fellowship, Inc.
content: Our #StaffoftheMonth returns, and this time it is our beloved Senior Manager of Data, Operations, & Tech, Madeline Vera! She’s been with us since almost the beginning of TKH and has been a pivotal #teammember to our org to keep us running as smoothly as possible. She wears many hats and always makes time for others when they need her. She’s been someone who demonstrates leadership skills that many of us strive to have and has been a rock to many of us here.Congrats, Madeline! We are so proud of you and appreciate all you do to support this community.#StaffSpotlight #nonprofit #organization #staff #dreamteam #grateful #HappyFriday #TGIF

name: The Knowledge House Fellowship, Inc.
content: “Candidates are attracted to our program because we provide (1) an inclusive, high-quality, and part-time program that allows Fellows to still work during the day while pursuing their new path, and (2) a stipend to help students make ends meet, instead of charging $20,000 for a traditional coding boot camp. We partner with community-based organizations in our site cities to identify underestimated talent looking to transition into the tech industry,” says Daniel Adeyanju, Director of Programs at The Knowledge House.Invest in a fellow through one of our new monthly giving clubs today!

name: The Knowledge House Fellowship, Inc.
content: In response to the employment needs of America’s tech sector and #CommunitiesOfColor, The Knowledge House has embarked on a national expansion effort to reach job seekers where demand for #tech workers has increased but geographic disparities and #programming gaps limit access to these careers.This fall, TKH is launching a public #campaign to raise $2,500,000 toward supporting our Fellows. With your partnership, #technologists in #NYC, #Newark, #Atlanta, and #LosAngeles will receive an opportunity of a lifetime to achieve their dreams.If you are interested in volunteering, sponsoring or donating to #TheGreatRestoration Check out our Website.#ExpandOpportunity #nonprofit #TechTalent #POC

name: The Knowledge House Fellowship, Inc.
content: Nickala Epps, our Manager of Student Success, is this month's #StaffofTheMonth, and has been an inspiration for our students!She's always willing to help out with any project and is always dedicated to not only helping our #Fellows grow professionally, but also personally.
